text: I seen this 18 years ago when it first came out.  Only the title was Final Destination. This is the same thing in a different wrapper. Or at the very least, is pretty close to the Saw series of repeat wanna-be horror films. Sad how dry this generation's concept of "horror" truly is.  Almost no effort at all. Extremely limited imagination, and less than decent story-lines. Not one person in the film was intelligent enough to make the choice which would have stopped all of their nightmares.  Take a dare. Dare the other to kill the one that is killing them. In order to obey the rules which apparently could not be violated without death, the killer would have to show them-self. Simply kill it, ending the horribly written wanna-be final destination movie.
